ibits VMI History FAQs Genealogy   Alumni Manuscripts Civil War   New Market Library   Archives Preston Library Library Home Find Books Departments Media Equipment Technical Services Visitor Information Archives Archives Home Online Exhibits VMI History FAQs Genealogy   Alumni Manuscripts Civil War   New Market Preston Library Library Home Find Books Departments Media Equipment Technical Services Visitor Information Archives Archives Home Online Exhibits VMI History FAQs Genealogy   Alumni Manuscripts Civil War   New Market Preston Library Library Home Find Books Departments Media Equipment Technical Services Visitor Information Preston Library Preston Library Library Home Library Home Find Books Find Books Departments Departments Media Equipment Media Equipment Technical Services Technical Services Visitor Information Visitor Information Archives Archives Home Online Exhibits VMI History FAQs Genealogy   Alumni Manuscripts Civil War   New Market Archives Archives Archives Home Archives Home Online Exhibits Online Exhibits VMI History FAQs VMI History FAQs Genealogy   Alumni Genealogy   Alumni Manuscripts Manuscripts Civil War   New Market Civil War   New Market Give Give Close Menu Home   Administrative Offices   Finance   Administration   HR   Physical Education Faculty Position Physical Education Faculty Position December 16  2015  The Department of Physical Education at the Virginia Military Institute invites applications for an Assistant Professor position commencing 1 August 2016  This position is funded for a three year term with the potential for conversion to tenure track  The Department of Physical Education is a non degree granting service oriented program that also offers a minor in Exercise Science  The selected candidate will teach courses and activity classes in support of the general program  as well as courses for the newly developed Exercise Science Minor  Applicants must be able to teach Exercise Physiology  and a variety of exercise science courses and laboratories  In addition  the selected candidate is expected to engage in scholarly work  committee assignments  and service assignments within the Institute to include assisting with the facilitation of an outdoor experiential program for cadets  Requirements for the position include a Ph D  or Ed D  in physical education  or a related field  and a strong commitment to undergraduate teaching  VMI is a state supported  coeducational  national liberal arts college of 1700 students with a strong commitment to produce educated  responsible citizens  VMI faculty and students wear military uniforms  but no prior military experience is required  Applicants should submit CV  letter of application  three letters of recommendation and official transcripts  Interested candidates must apply on line at http virginiajobs peopleadmin com postings 31041 Review of applications will continue until the position is filled  In a continuing effort to enrich its academic environment and provide equal educational and employment opportunities  VMI encourages women  minorities  disabled individuals and veterans to apply  AmeriCorps  Peace Corps and other national service alumni are also encouraged to apply Home   Administrative Offices   Finance   Administration   HR   Physical Education Faculty Position Physical Education Faculty Position December 16  2015  The Department of Physical Education at the Virginia Military Institute invites applications for an Assistant Professor position commencing 1 August 2016  This position is funded for a three year term with the potential for conversion to tenure track  The Department of Physical Education is a non degree granting service oriented program that also offers a minor in Exercise Science  The selected candidate will teach courses and activity classes in support of the general program  as well as courses for the newly developed Exercise Science Minor  Applicants must be able to teach Exercise Physiology  and a variety of exercise scienc